== Introduction ==

This is python-cli, a CLI construction toolit for Python. It is similar in
scope to Python's "cmd", "cmd2", and pyCLI. It has the following features:

 * Interactive and one-command modes
 * Can be used as a #! script interpreter
 * Shell redirects (including here-docs)
 * Pipelines
 * Shell commands (via "!")
 * Rigorous parser via PLY
 * Add commands by providing a Command subclass

== Installation ==

 $ python setup.py build
 $ python setup.py install

== Usage ==

See the "lib/cli/commands" directory for some examples.
